#Convert createdDate and Closed Date to dateTime
from datetime import datetime
dataset_nyc['Created Date'] = pd.to_datetime(dataset_nyc['Created Date']).dt.tz_localize(None)
dataset_nyc['Closed Date'] = pd.to_datetime(dataset_nyc['Closed Date']).dt.tz_localize(None)

#Create a column Request_Closing_Time with value = 'Closed Date'  - 'Created Date'
from datetime import datetime
dataset_nyc['Request_Closing_Time'] = dataset_nyc['Closed Date'] - dataset_nyc['Created Date']
print(dataset_nyc['Request_Closing_Time'].head(10))
# Convert the Request_Closing_Time to hours
dataset_nyc['Request_Closing_Time'] = ((dataset_nyc['Request_Closing_Time'].dt.seconds/60)/60)
dataset_nyc['Request_Closing_Time'].fillna(0,inplace=True)
dataset_nyc['Request_Closing_Time'] = dataset_nyc['Request_Closing_Time'].astype(int)

In [274]:
#performing oneway annova on all complaint-type
f_val, p_val = stats.f_oneway(
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Animal Abuse')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Animal in a Park')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Bike/Roller/Skate Chronic')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Blocked Driveway')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Derelict Vehicle')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Disorderly Youth')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Drinking')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Ferry Complaint')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Graffiti')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Homeless Encampment')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Illegal Fireworks')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Noise - Commercial')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Noise - House of Worship')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Noise - Park')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Noise - Street/Sidewalk')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Noise - Vehicle')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Panhandling')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Posting Advertisement')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Squeegee')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Noise - Park')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Traffic')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Urinating in Public')['Request_Closing_Time'], 
grouped_closingtime.get_group('Vending')['Request_Closing_Time']
 )  
 
print( "ANOVA results: F=", f_val, ", P =", p_val)   

# ANOVA. pvalue is almost 0 and F-score is large showing strong correlation
## Null Hypothesis- there's no correlation between complaint type and request_closing_time
## based on f-val and p-val, we reject the null hpyothesis.

ANOVA results: F= 444.3105975707488 , P = 0.0

#chi-Square testing is used when both the varibales are categorical.
from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency
import scipy.stats

scipy.stats.chisquare(df_gptest2['Complaint Type'].value_counts())

scipy.stats.chisquare(df_gptest2['City'].value_counts())

cont = pd.crosstab(df_gptest2['Complaint Type'],
                   df_gptest2['City'])

scipy.stats.chi2_contingency(cont)

## Null Hypothesis- there's no correlation between complaint type and City
## p-val is 0.0 suggesting high correlation between complaint type and the City, 
#we reject the null hpyothesis.
